  "body": "We should also define ways to test improvements to peering in specific network scenarios before making any large changes.\n\nFor example, joining a small, existing network where other nodes are at max peer capacity; staying connected on a noisy / malicious network where we have nodes that are constantly trying to saturate our connections (eclipse attack).\n\nIdeally, we would have regularly running benchmarks which keep metrics on these scenarios. (Note: this may be a good use case for Kubernetes, as there are some nice testing tools that we can use there to simulate various environmental issues, like jitter, packet loss, unreliable nodes, etc.).\n",
